// Fine-tuning is the process of taking a general-purpose AI model and specializing it for specific tasks or behaviors after its initial training.
// While a base model might have learned general language patterns from the entire internet, fine-tuning teaches it to follow instructions better, adopt a particular conversational style, or excel at specific tasks like writing code, answering medical questions, or maintaining a consistent personality.
// This is why ChatGPT doesn't just generate random internet-like text but instead helpfully answers your questions—it has been fine-tuned on examples of helpful conversations—and it's also how companies create specialized versions of these models for specific industries or use cases without having to train an entirely new model from scratch.
